Chapter 1: The Weight of the Unseen
The Onyxspire Academy was a marvel of white marble and gold, floating high above the smog-choked slums of Valerius. Inside, the air was sweet and thin. Outside, the world was dying.
Cyprian didn't belong in the marble halls. He was a "Janitorial Squire," an E-Rank Null whose only job was to scrub the mana-scorch marks off the training room floors after the elite students were finished playing at being heroes.
"Missed a spot, Scrub," a voice sneered.
Cyprian didn't look up. He knew the voice. Dante Valerius, the heir to the city's founding house. Dante was an [A-Rank: Sun-Bringer]. He stood there in his silk uniform, smelling of expensive spices, his palm glowing with a gentle, condescending light.
"My apologies, Lord Dante," Cyprian muttered, his rag dripping with grey cleaning fluid.
"It’s a shame, really," Dante continued, stepping on Cyprian’s wet rag. "The System gave you a window, but no Class. You're like a spectator at your own funeral."
Cyprian looked at his own reflection in the polished floor. His Status Window was a mocking, empty blur.
